                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "version": 1,
                "textFormat": 0,
                "textStyle": "",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A Peugeot VIN Check is a unique code assigned to each Peugeot vehicle, serving as a distinctive identifier that contains crucial information about the car’s specifications, manufacturing details, and history.",
                    "format": 0,
                    "version": 1,
                    "detail": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "direction": "ltr",
                "format": "",
                "indent": 0,
                "version": 1,
                "textFormat": 0,
                "textStyle": "",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The Peugeot VIN is typically composed of 17 alphanumeric characters and can be found on the vehicle’s chassis or in its associated documents. By performing a Peugeot VIN lookup, individuals can access valuable data such as the car’s model, engine type, production year, country of origin, and additional optional features.",
                    "format": 0,
                    "version": 1,
                    "detail": 0,
                    "mode": "normal",
                    "style": ""
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "mediaType": "image",
        "reverse": false
      }
    ]
  },
